    <thetext>AptCompilationParticipant registers a ResourceChangeListener with this comment:

		// Bug 180107: there is no CompilationParticipant.buildComplete() method,
		// so we have to use a resource change listener instead.
		IResourceChangeListener listener = new IResourceChangeListener() {
			public void resourceChanged(IResourceChangeEvent event) {
				buildComplete();
			}
		};

I think at the time this code was written, there was no CompilationParticipant.buildFinished() so this workaround was necessary. Now we can use CompilationParticipant.buildFinished()</thetext>
